<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-02-18T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-02-18T07:00:00-05:00" n="711" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d711">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/8972: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-18T12:00:00+00:00">February 18,
                                            1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 18—10:55
                                        a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>319. Jules Henry said to me last night that Negrin and Del Vayo
                                    were now ready to accept immediate surrender provided Franco
                                    would agree that there should not be executions by way of
                                    reprisal. Jules Henry said that the latest news from Burgos
                                    indicated that Franco would refuse this proviso and insist on
                                    immediate unconditional surrender. The French Government
                                    believed that Negrin and his supporters in Valencia and Madrid
                                    therefore would fight to the bitter end because surrender would
                                    mean firing squads.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>